removePosition(bytes32[] storage,bytes32.details: - assumes `id` is stored only once in the `positions` array. if `id` occurs twice, debt would be double counted.

params.id: - the hash id of the credit line to be removed from active ids after removePosition() has run
params.ids: - all current credit lines on the Line of Credit facility

returns._0: newPositions - all active credit lines on the Line of Credit facility after the `id` has been removed [Bob - consider renaming to newIds

stepQ(bytes32[] storage).details: - Must perform check for ids[0] being valid (non-zero) before calling

params.ids: - all current credit lines on the Line of Credit facility

returns._0: swapped  - returns true if the swap has occurred

removePosition(bytes32[] storage,bytes32.notice: - Removes a position id from the active list of open positions.

stepQ(bytes32[] storage).notice: - swap the first element in the queue, provided it is null, with the next available valid(non-null) id
